      "created_at": "2024-10-09T16:39:37.669Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Some trainers work better with low RPM than others, you also can try shifting to an easier gear to see if it helps a bit but if it is too easy then you wont be able hit the target watts.  You just need to be very steady at these low RPMs to make sure it does not go too low as you pointed out it can become impossibly high resistance.</p>",
